		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=158562"><span id=>thergreatbob</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>8 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=thergreatbob&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Ok, I'm on a non-pvp server, and I know they are supposed to be friendly places where everyone gets along, but let's face it, there will always be one or two people that do something that really just completely enrage you. I play a few chars on the Karana server, a monk a wizard, and an enchater. I give free ports, free clairity's to everyone I see, if I see anyone struggling, I love to help them out, but I have come across this one druid in particular, with my Iksar monk, that I wish to get revenge on in the form getting him killed repeatedly. Let me relate my difficulties with you. <br><br>I was&nbsp;&nbsp;with a friend hunting in Perma looking for an unholy coldstone for my bronze shackle quest, and we got hit by a train. suffice it to say, we both were killed, me because by some cruel bit of luck, my FD fails and 3 gobby wizards procede to nuke me back to my bind point. My friend had to log, and so would recover his corpse at a later date. Me haveing FD maxed for lvl 30, I really am not worried about having any difficulties getting it back myself. Anyway.... I was bound in Gfay (was doing a bit of faction work before) and ran to BB to look for a friendly druid to port me to SFG as it is the closest port to perma. I waited for a while shouting and no replies, so I ran around killing gobbies and snakes for fun when I see a druid shouting &quot;porting for donations&quot; and that he was going to whatever the 29 port locations are, which includes SFG, so I told him I needed a port for a corpse run, but I could pay (gotta love that being KOS to the banker in Felwithe still doesn't stop me from banking there =P). He was happy to get a paying customer, and I politely asked that he invis me first, as Iksars are quite KOS in SFG, though I didn't tell him that, but come on people, he wasn't foreign, and do you really expect to get to lvl 29 without knowing that iksars are evil? Well, he said ok. I got to the druid ring and said ok, ready to go, make sure you invis first. He began to cast a spell, which I expected to be invis, but lo and behold, he cast his port spell instead. Well, I knew I was probably screwed, but I made an attempt to get FD'd before the SFG guards realized I was there, but alas, I was too slow. at lv 30 I only have about 800 HP or so, and before I could do anything I'm hit 3 times by blows dealing 300+ damage each. Well, I'm sure you can do the math... that is a bit more HP than I have. So, back in Gfay again, and I ask him, why didn't you invis me BEFORE the port like I asked you to multiple times? He replied with oh, You should have been more clear that you wanted the invis first. Of course I'm  getting pretty mad now, but I try to be a calm guy, anyway, I reply by saying I'm an Iksar, and just like all evil races, I'm KOS at druid rings with druids (not 100% sure on that, but seemed a logical response at the time), I needed an invis first so I wouldn't be attacked the moment I zoned in. He again replied with oh, well, you still should have specified it more clearly that you wanted invis before the port. At this time I'm getting extremely mad. I really didn't care about the xp loss, I didn't care about the need to pay for another port, my monk does fine as is being funded by my main for all porting needs, the only real reason I was mad was because of his utter lack of intelligence. A few seconds later I recieved a message from him saying &quot;well , F@#$ you&quot;. He then proceded to disband the group. Now he hadn't gotten my money yet, but he had wasted my time and angered me by his negligence. <br><br>I'm am not that easily angered, and the only form of revenge I currently have is a &quot;no port/clarity list&quot; for people that anger me. Doesn't really harm them much, and acts as a release for my anger. This guy, to me, seems to deserve a far harsher future. I guess what this entire post, or rant is for is  to ask of you good ways to get him killed. He is lvl 29, and I am fairly twinked, so I should be able to  lvl much faster than him if need be, but I do tend to spend most of my time on my main. My plee here is to ask of you all to post succesfull revenge stories, or ideas on ways for me to reap my revenge from this Drood. <br><br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >3 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
