		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.70]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=GLASS&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I agree that it's probably not worth the trouble, but I have a tendency to be an evil SOB from time to time and so I have some ideas for you.&nbsp;&nbsp;Fortunately, you play 3 classes that are tailor made for this type of thing.<br><br>Monk first.  FD is your friend.  The obvious way here is to pull a big train of nasties and park them on this guys front porch as you plop to the ground.  Then sit and laugh as he gets walloped.  SoW is helpful for this.<br><br>Enchanter.  This is one of my favorites.  It can be done anywhere but WC is a great and obvious spot for this.  The tricky part is to get the two druids that hang out near the rings both mezzed.  Once this is done, run over to your victim and bestow upon him the kindness of a clarity.  He will thank you profusely.  Then, get the hell out of Dodge.  Once the two druids wake up, he will be on their hate list from you buffing him.  Note:  You may want to bind yourself at the WC zone line just inside of Kith, that way you can gate before your mezzes wear off and hopefully even zone back in in enough time to catch your friend getting pummeled by the two druids.<br><br>Lastly, druids.  Albeit this only works well in cases like your original one.  I've never played a druid but always fantasized about the sheer abuse of the power of porting.  Taking newbies straight into DL, dropping Iksars and Trolls in Surefall, porting my group to some random location and disbanding when I decide I've gotten enough xp for the day.  I know, I know, that second idea for druids hits pretty close to home for you.  Well, I said it would be fun, I never said I had ever done it.  I've never even played a druid, but have gotten my Iksar monk ported into West Karana without an invis first.  Yeah, it sucks.  But c'mon, it would be fun to be on the other side once or twice.<br><br>I probably spend way too much time thinking about stuff like this, but messing with other people is hella fun if you ask me.  After all, it is a roleplaying game.  There are people in real life who cause grief for no other apparent reason than just to cause the grief.  Why wouldn't there be such people in Norrath?  Besides, it's still a game and people that take it way too seriously need a reality check every once in a while.  <br><br>have fun,<br><br>-Yizz</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=10192549388616&num=3&page=&post=1&mid=10192549388616><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">3 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class3">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
